{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-express-concerns/task-116","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"learn-how-to-express-concerns","challengeType":19,"description":"","nodules":null,"explanation":"<section id=\"explanation\">\n<p>Maria koristi <strong>indirektan govor</strong> nakon <span class=\"highlighted-text\">they said</span> kako bi prenela ono što je tim ranije rekao. U indirektnom govoru glagoli se često prebacuju u prošlo vreme, ali <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Present Continuous</span> (<span class=\"highlighted-text\">are putting</span>) ostaje u trajnom obliku (<span class=\"highlighted-text\">they're already putting in extra hours</span>). Na primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Direktni link: <span class=\"highlighted-text\">\"We are working late,\" they said.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Usemi ulioripotiwa: <span class=\"highlighted-text\">They said they were working late.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Evo još jednog primera:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Direktan izraz: <span class=\"highlighted-text\">\"I have finished the report,\" she said.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Izveštana upotreba: <span class=\"highlighted-text\">She said she had finished the report.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>","helpCategory":"English","instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Slušaj audio i odgovori na pitanje koje se nalazi dole.</p>\n</section>","fields":{"slug":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-express-concerns/task-116"},"questions":[{"text":"<p>Zašto tim misli da je krajnji rok previše kratak, prema Mariji?</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p>Zato što još nisu počeli da rade na projektu.</p>","feedback":"<p>Maria kaže da već rade na projektu.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p>Zato što već rade više sati.</p>","feedback":null,"audioId":null},{"answer":"<p>Zato što veruju da je rok previše daleko.</p>","feedbac